A hyper-realistic, retro-styled poster for a female buddy cop duo titled “Rosemary & Thyme”, designed like a 1970s cop show one-sheet. The two detectives stand front and center, exuding tough but cool charisma in classic plains clothes: wide-lapel leather jackets, flared pants, aviator shades, and stylish boots. One is a fiery redhead with sharp, determined eyes; the other a confident blonde with a sly, knowing smirk. Both brandish sleek revolvers and display polished police badges, held with authority.
Behind them, a gritty 1970s cityscape stretches out—graffiti-marked brick walls, neon signs, and the hazy glow of streetlights at dusk. Vintage cars, boxy and chrome-trimmed, line the curb, while blurred silhouettes suggest the bustle of crime and nightlife.
The title “Rosemary & Thyme” blazes across the bottom in bold, authentic 1970s cop show typography—chunky serif letters, slightly distressed, in vibrant orange and yellow gradients, with subtle halftone print texture for a true period feel.
The composition has a cinematic, 85mm lens look with shallow depth of field: razor-sharp focus on the detectives, soft falloff into the urban background. Skin textures, clothing fabrics, and metallic details of the guns and badges are rendered in ultra-sharp realism. The overall atmosphere radiates retro grit meets stylish cool, like a lost classic buddy-cop TV show poster.
